      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Rate Pay.....that's what it is. Many jobs are based on &amp;quot;rate pay&amp;quot;, they have a set number of items you should be able to make in an hour. You get a bonus for each item over that rate. How do you set the &amp;quot;tank rate&amp;quot;. It isn't just &amp;quot;warriors&amp;quot; that set it, but a certain level/geared/aa'd warrior that sets it. It might not even be that, it might be the general progression of all the classes.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; In that set up, if the &amp;quot;tank rate&amp;quot; is Time level warrior, then knights who are rated as Qivic,Tacvi, Anguish or Demi. Will technically tank better in a time rated zone because they have better gear, more aa, higher levels. I suspect that &amp;quot;tank rate&amp;quot; on new expansions are based on warriors at the top of the last exspansion. That would make the new content challangeing for warriors and  difficult for knights. Until knights managed to become &amp;quot;tank rated&amp;quot; for that exspansion, by gearing up, gaining aa's and spells.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; Downward scaleing is a real obstical for warriors because they lack the ability to improve thier &amp;quot;tank rate&amp;quot; much above the quota. Where knights can be way above  quota &amp;quot;rates&amp;quot;.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
